text_blocks.snippet: Phil Collins is currently 75 years old (born January 30, 1951). He is presently living in retirement in Geneva, Switzerland, where he reportedly receives 24-hour nursing care due to ongoing health issues.
Collins is recognized as a world-class musician whose proficiency led to his induction into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame twice (as a solo artist and member of Genesis).

list.snippet: Occupations: Session drummer, band member (Genesis, Brand X), solo performer.

Proficiency: Mastery. Ranked #43 on Rolling Stone's 100 Greatest Drummers of All Time and inducted into the Modern Drummer Hall of Fame. He pioneered the "gated reverb" drum sound that defined the 1980s.
Note: He no longer plays professionally due to spinal nerve damage and arthritis.
Proficiency: Expert. Achieved seven US #1 solo singles and one with Genesis. Known for an emotionally vulnerable, soulful tenor voice capable of high-energy pop and intimate ballads.
Occupations: Songwriter, film score composer (e.g., Disney's Tarzan).
Proficiency: Exceptional. Inducted into the Songwriters Hall of Fame in 2003. He won an Academy Award for "You'll Be in My Heart".
Proficiency: Advanced. Produced nearly all of his solo albums and multiple albums for artists like Eric Clapton and Robert Plant.
Proficiency: Professional. While primarily known as a drummer, he played nearly all instruments (including keyboards and drum machines like the Roland TR-808) on his solo album Both Sides.
Actor: Began as a child actor in the West End (Oliver!) and starred in films like Buster (1988) and guest-starred on Miami Vice.
Author: Published his autobiography, Not Dead Yet, in 2016.
